We need to break through, remove the stigma, invest in programs like telemedicine and outpatient care, invest in the next generation of young leaders willing to serve in these rural communities that have been left behind, and remove the corrupting influence of money politics.
Here in Iowa, managed care organizations have created serious pitfalls in an already struggling mental health industry and those special interests have politicians in their back pockets.
As a result we see our friends and neighbors, often unnoticed, with serious mental health issues, stigmatized by the idea of seeking help, and facing a serious lack of available resources.
We had to deal with these issues at the county level, and I hear too many stories about the shortfalls of mental health care services, especially in rural communities. https://t.co/3wbqnaXzUZ
